Date:  0/0/1995
Source:  Which Coastal Plant?
Author:  CROWE
Vol / Page:  32
Edition:
Quote:  A native of the South-West Cape area of South Africa, introduced to New Zealand in the nineteenth century as a garden plant suitable for covering dry banks and poor sandy soil in frost-free areas. However, birds soon spread the seed, and by 1870 boneseed was noticed escaping into the wild.
